docs.abstract: Sanitary Inspector M. Cochran Maltreated by Smugglers
docs.lead_paragraph: JACKSONVILLE, Fla., Nov. 30. -- A special to the Times-Union from Punta Gorda says: "The report has just reached here of an outrage committed upon the Port Sanitary Inspector for this district, Morris Cochran, by a band of smugglers from Cuba. The affair happened far down the harbor, and the details are meagre. The report says that Cochran boarded a Spanish schooner near Lacosta Key and asked to see her papers.

docs.lead_paragraph: NEW-HAVEN, Aug. 20. -- The sloop yacht Hattie of New-York, with seven men on board, struck on the New-Haven Breakwater about 10:30 o'clock last night, in the heavy storm and fog which then prevailed, and went to pieces in a very few moments. The men had not time to save anything and barely managed, after desperate struggling in the water, to reach the breakwater.
